Context: The Community Club series is an initiative for students at George Brown College where they can explore various forms of communication and learn effective listening skills. These clubs are student-led, and students will have the opportunity to learn from mental health practitioners to help develop meaningful and practical goals for personal growth. Interested individuals can register and learn more about peer mentor wellness programs and land acknowledgment. The contact information for inquiries is 416-415-2000 (voice) or 1-877-515-5559 (TTY), and emails can be sent to ask.george@georgebrown.ca. More information, including application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and other details, can be obtained by signing up on the website. The content of this website is subject to change without notice. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
